# Frontend Configuration Template
# Copy this file to .env and update with your actual values

# =============================================================================
# BACKEND API CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# URL where your Flask backend is hosted
# This URL will be used by the frontend to make API calls
#
# Local Development Example:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000
#
# Cloud Production Examples:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.your-domain.com
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-domain.com/api
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - All Vite environment variables must start with VITE_ to be exposed to the browser
# - Never commit the actual .env file with production URLs to version control
# - Update this URL to match your backend deployment URL in production
# - The backend must have proper CORS settings to allow requests from your frontend domain
# - After changing .env, restart the Vite dev server for changes to take effect
